Title : National Foundation of Museums of Morocco
Text : {{Orphan|date=May 2014}}

The '''National Foundation of Museums of the Kingdom of Morocco''' was created in 2011. Under Law 01.09 governing this foundation, the national museums previously managed by the Ministry of Culture, were entrusted to its tutelage on February 2014.
 
Chaired by [[Mehdi Qotbi]], The National Foundation of Museums of the Kingdom of Morocco is a non-for-profit institution invested legal personality and financial autonomy, called to strengthen the governance of the national museums it manages on behalf of the government.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.leconomiste.com/article/889779-fondation-nationale-des-museesbrmehdi-qotbi-veut-se-mettre-vite-au-travail |title=Fondation nationale des Musées Mehdi Qotbi veut se mettre vite au travail |publisher=Leconomiste.com |date=2011-12-21 |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref>

==Missions==
The promotion of culture, as well as the strengthening, the preservation and the enhancement of the cultural and artistic Moroccan heritage  are part of the main goals of the Foundation.<ref name="lematin1">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.lematin.ma/journal/2014/entretien-avec-mehdi-qotbi-president-de-la-fondation-nationale-des-musees_-la-promotion-du-patrimoine-museographique-national-va--de-pair-avec-la-valorisation-de-la-culture-et-de-l-art-marocains-/199075.html |title=Entretien avec Mehdi Qotbi, président de la Fondation nationale des musées : "La promotion du patrimoine muséographique national va de pair avec la valorisation de la culture et de l'art marocains |publisher=Le Matin.Ma |date= |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref>
The promotion of culture, as well as the strengthening, the preservation and the enhancement of the cultural and artistic Moroccan heritage  are part of the main goals of the Foundation.<ref name="lematin1"/>
* Enhance the national museums from the level of restoration of the buildings to upgrading the exhibition conditions and the existing collections ;
* Improve the administrative and financial management practices of the national museums;
* Create a platform for communication and develop supports around the content of these museums;
* Implement an acquisition program  and keep an inventory documentation of the existing collections ;
* Commit to cultural diplomacy by promoting dialogue and exchange between different countries.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://adala.justice.gov.ma/production/html/Fr/liens/..%5C174770.htm# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-04-28 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140424141820/http://adala.justice.gov.ma/production/html/Fr/liens/..%5C174770.htm# |archive-date=2014-04-24 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
Since its creation, the National Foundation of Museums of the Kingdom of Morocco has focused on implementing necessary structures and procedures to ensure proper functioning, as well as elaborating ambitious strategic planning through 2025.<ref name="lematin1"/>

==Partners==
The National Foundation of Museums of the Kingdom of Morocco has also signed several partnerships with prestigious international institutions. Among them, the [[Louvre]] Museum,<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.lnt.ma/culture-maroc/le-louvre-sassocie-a-la-fondation-nationale-des-musees-97275.html|title=Le Louvre s'associe à la Fondation Nationale des musées - La Nouvelle Tribune|publisher=Lnt.ma|date=|accessdate=2015-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426222021/http://www.lnt.ma/culture-maroc/le-louvre-sassocie-a-la-fondation-nationale-des-musees-97275.html#|archive-date=2014-04-26|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> the [[Museum of European and Mediterranean Civilisations]] (Mucem),<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://videos.tf1.fr/jt-20h/2014/les-splendeurs-de-volubilis-s-exposent-a-marseille-8396098.html |title=Le Mucem de Marseille accueille l'exposition Volubilis - Le journal de 20h - Replay |publisher=Videos.tf1.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref> or the [[Arab World Institute]] (IMA).<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.lematin.ma/journal/2014/-moi-marocaineana-maghribia-_une-initiative-pour-encourager-la-creativite/200026.html |title="Moi, Marocain(e)/Ana Maghribi(a)" : Une initiative pour encourager la créativité |publisher=Le Matin.Ma |date= |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref> These partnerships have allowed the implementation of major exhibitions, as " The splendors of Volubilis " at the Mucem,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mucem.org/en/node/2442 |title=The Splendours of Volubilis &#124; MuCEM - Musée des civilisations de l'Europe et de la Méditerranée |publisher=MuCEM |date=2014-08-25 |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref> " Morocco of the thousand colours " at the IMA, and "The medieval Morocco, an empire from Africa to the Spain " at the Museum of the [[Louvre]], take will both take place next autumn.
During a visit to New York and Washington in March 2014, the President of the Foundation had the opportunity to meet senior officials of the National Foundation of the [[Smithsonian]], the [[Metropolitan Museum]] and the [[Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum]]. They talked about the wish of [[Morocco]] to democratize access to culture and to make it affordable to all Moroccans. All these American institutions agreed to assist in the future the Foundation in the areas of museums, the training of human resources management, and the restoration and conservation of our heritage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.medias24.com/map/map-488-Mehdi-Qotbi-a-New-York-pour-la-cooperation-avec-les-Musees-les-plus-prestigieux-au-monde.html |title=Mehdi Qotbi à New York pour la coopération avec les Musées les plus prestigieux au monde |publisher=Medias24.com |date= |accessdate=2015-03-04}}</ref>

